  "prompt": "What are the best places to eat vegetarian food in New Delhi?",
  "response": "New Delhi is home to a vibrant culinary scene with plenty of excellent vegetarian options. Here are some of the best places to enjoy vegetarian food in the city:\n\n1. **Bukhara** - Situated in the ITC Maurya Hotel, this renowned restaurant serves North Indian cuisine with a focus on tandoori dishes, including a variety of vegetarian specialties.\n\n2. **Saravana Bhavan** - A popular South Indian chain known for its delicious dosas, idlis, and thalis. It\u2019s an excellent spot for a casual meal.\n\n3. **SodaBottleOpenerWala** - This quirky Bombay-style cafe offers a range of vegetarian Parsi dishes along with Mumbai street food, in a lively atmosphere.\n\n4. **Haveli** - Located in the heart of the city, this restaurant provides a traditional Punjabi experience with a wide array of vegetarian dishes, served in a rustic ambiance.\n\n5. **The Green Room** - A cozy eatery known for its healthy vegetarian options, including salads, smoothies, and a range of global cuisines.\n\n6. **Gupta's** - This iconic eatery is known for its North Indian vegetarian offerings, including chole bhature and various curries.\n\n7. **Rajasthani Thali at Chokhi Dhani** - This restaurant provides an immersive experience with Rajasthani cuisine served in a traditional style, offering a colorful thali with a wide range of dishes.\n\n8. **Moolchand Paranthe Wala** - Famous for its stuffed parathas served with an assortment of pickles and curd, this street-side stall is a must-visit for a quick meal.\n\n9. **Cafe Lota** - Located within the National Crafts Museum, this cafe serves innovative Indian dishes with a focus on fresh and local ingredients in a beautiful setting.\n\n10. **Pind Balluchi** - Offering a rustic Punjabi ambiance, this restaurant features an extensive menu of vegetarian northern Indian dishes.\n\nThese spots cater to different tastes and budgets, ensuring that you'll find something delicious regardless of your culinary preferences.",
